column3: Number of hits it counts as in combo
column4: For attacks which hit multiple times, with each hit having scaling calculated separately. Also used for moves with follow ups or target combos.
column5: the second multiplier in a scaling route for this attack. e.g. all light attacks deal 100% damage by default, but then damage drops to 80% for the next attack in the string. Therefore the scaling route is 0.8
column6: Additional scaling to be added or subtracted from the scaling route scaling for the next move
column7: As previous but for the  current move
column8: Miniumum scaling which can be applied to the move. Only applies to supers. Ranges from 0.3 to 0.5
column9: If the first move in the string is a counter hit, applies this multiplier to the attacks damage
column10: If the first move in the string is a punish counter hit, applies this multiplier to the attacks damage
column11: How much drive gauge is recovered when this attack hits
column12: Whether the attack is visible in the move selection dropdown. Hidden moves are follow ups for special moves or target combos which require scaling calculations done separately to the main attack
